\title{\texttt{textmin} Clustering}
\author{Ingo Feinerer}
\date{}
\begin{document}
\maketitle

This document shows typical text clustering examples that can be
performed with \texttt{textmin}.

\section*{Initialization}
<<>>=
library(textmin)
tdcl <- textdoccol("../../ext/data/reuters21578/", "REUT21578", TRUE, TRUE)
tdm <- termdocmatrix(tdcl)
@
creates a text document collection and the term-document matrix for
it.
\section*{Hierarchical Clustering}
<<>>=
hcl <- hclust(dist(tdm))
@
performs a hierarchical clustering on the distance matrix of the original
term-document matrix. The visualized result looks like:
<<fig=TRUE>>=
plot(hcl)
@
\section*{$k$-means Clustering}
<<>>=
kmeans(tdm, 2)
@
performs a $k$-means clustering with $2$ clusters on the term-document matrix.
\section*{Spectral clustering}
The following example shows a spectral clustering of the text
document collection with String Kernels form the
\texttt{kernlab} package.
<<>>=
library(kernlab)
stringkern <- stringdot(type = "string")
specc(tdcl, 2, kernel = stringkern)
@
